19, Male, White, 6ft, 185 lbs, issue located in the brain, issue present lifelong, history of OCD/intrusive thoughts and depression. Not a smoker but uses marijuana.

Recently, I’ve been researching Aspergers and I think I may be on the spectrum. Here’s a list of symptoms I exhibit, I’ll try to keep it brief:

-Mushy textures make me gag, sometimes to the point that I hurl.

-I speak a lot about what interests me and find myself bored when people talk about something else.

-I bring up conversation at inappropriate time.

-I get really annoyed when my planned schedule is interrupted or I am asked to go somewhere I don’t want to go.

-People like me because I am funny but it seems that when I develop friendship I have trouble maintaining that friendship.

-I sometimes make very off color and inappropriate remarks that clearly bother people but when I say them they sound normal too me.

-I sometimes stutter over my words. I can keep a good flow in my sentence but that will break with a stutter even though I know what I’m trying to say, I just can’t word it.

-My facial expression is usually the same or is sometimes very exaggerated to appear as if I’m interested in the conversation/situation.

-I avoid eye contact a lot with people I don’t know and get anxious when I give them eye contact. However, with people I’m comfortable with that isn’t a problem.

-Very attentive memory, I tend to be able to memorize a lot of details of things my friends/peers cannot. For example, my memory of roads is very accurate.

-Sensitivity to sounds, I feel physical pain/itching/cringing when I hear certain high pitches noise. 

-I don’t mind hanging out with people, but I also don’t mind social isolation.

I can’t tell if I’m overthinking and just maybe think I have Aspergers, or I actually have Aspergers. There’s a lot of “stereotypical” symptoms I don’t exhibit, for example, I’m an average math student. I also can socialize relatively well. However, I know everyone is different in how they display Aspergers. How do I go about testing? I have a psychiatrist.
